<TITLE> Govt gives another shake to administration </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com)  The government has transferred a number of officials with the rank of joint secretary and deputy secretary , according to a government statement. The establishment ministry issued the transfer orders on Sunday. Hasan Imam, joint secretary of the communications ministry, has been made member secretary of the National Pay Commission on deputation. The services of deputy secretary Alim Uddin Ahmed at the civil aviation and tourism ministry, and deputy secretary Mainul Islam, officer on special duty, have been placed under the finance ministry. They will be appointed to the National Pay Commission on deputation. Khandaker Iftekhar Haider, director of Bangladesh Small and Cottage Industries Corporation, has been transferred to the communications ministry as joint secretary. OSD joint secretary Prakash Chandra Das has been made director of the BSCIC on deputation. M Abduj Zaher, senior directing staff (civil) of the National Defence College, has been withdrawn and placed under the establishment ministry. Joint secretary AFM Nurus Safa Chowdhury, OSD, a trainee at a course at the National Defence College, has been deputed as senior directing staff (civil) of the college. bdne
